  <Name>k__BackingField: 2 Timothy
  fancyName: 
  nickname: 2ti
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 69cda689d36a6b64ca4a020e1d829e9f, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Introduction'
      title: Introduction
      number: 1
      content: "From Paul, an apostle of Jesus the Messiah, appointed by God\u2019s
        pleasure to announce the wonderful promise of life found in Jesus, the anointed
        Messiah."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "My beloved son, I pray for a greater release of God\u2019s grace,
        love, and total well-being to flow into your life from God our Father and
        from our Lord Jesus Christ!"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "You know that I\u2019ve been called to serve the God of my fathers
        with a clean conscience. Night and day I pray constantly for you, building
        a memorial for you with my prayers. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "I know that you have wept for me, your spiritual father, and your
        tears are dear to me. I can\u2019t wait to see you again! I\u2019m filled
        with joy "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Timothy and the Holy Spirit'
      title: Timothy and the Holy Spirit
      number: 5
      content: "as I think of your strong faith that was passed down through your
        family line. It began with your grandmother Lois, who passed it on to your
        dear mother, Eunice. And it\u2019s clear that you too are following in the
        footsteps of their godly example."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "I\u2019m writing to encourage you to fan into a flame and rekindle
        [[COMMENT(0)]] the fire of the spiritual gift God imparted to you when I
        laid my hands upon you. "
      comments:
      - number: 1:6
        content: "  Literally \u201Cexcite the gift\u201D or \u201Cawake the gift.\u201D    "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For God will never give you the spirit of fear, [[COMMENT(0)]] but
        the Holy Spirit who gives you mighty power, love, and self-control.   '
      comments:
      - number: 1:7
        content: "  That is, fearing men. The fear of God prevents us from fearing
          others.      The Aramaic can also be translated \u201Crevelation-light,\u201D
          or \u201Cinstruction.\u201D    "
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So never be ashamed of the testimony of our Lord, nor be embarrassed
        over my imprisonment, but overcome every evil by the revelation of the power
        of God! [[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: 1:8
        content: "  Or \u201Cwith the gospel and the power of God.\u201D    "
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "He gave us resurrection life [[COMMENT(0)]] and drew us to himself
        by his holy calling on our lives. And it wasn\u2019t because of any good
        we have done, but by his divine pleasure and marvelous grace that confirmed
        our union with the anointed Jesus, even before time began!   "
      comments:
      - number: 1:9
        content: "  Or \u201CHe is our life-giver.\u201D      Literally \u201Cbefore
          the time of the ages.\u201D    "
    - name: '10: Paul and His Gospel Ministry'
      title: Paul and His Gospel Ministry
      number: 10
      content: This truth is now being unveiled by the revelation of the anointed
        Jesus, our life-giver, who has dismantled death, obliterating all its effects
        on our lives, and has manifested his immortal life in us by the gospel.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And he has anointed [[COMMENT(0)]] me as his preacher, his apostle,
        and his teacher of truth to the nations. '
      comments:
      - number: 1:11
        content: "  Or \u201Cconsecrated.\u201D    "
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "The confidence of my calling enables me to overcome every difficulty
        without shame, for I have an intimate revelation of this God. And my faith
        in him convinces me that he is more than able to keep all that I\u2019ve
        placed in his hands [[COMMENT(0)]] safe and secure until the fullness of
        his appearing."
      comments:
      - number: 1:12
        content: "  Or \u201Cwhat he has entrusted to me.\u201D    "
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Allow the healing words you\u2019ve heard from me to live in you
        and make them a model for life as your faith and love for the Anointed One
        grows even more. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Guard well this incomparable treasure by the Spirit of Holiness living
        within you.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Perhaps you\u2019ve heard that Phygelus, [[COMMENT(0)]] and Hermogenes 
        and all the believers of Asia have deserted me because of my imprisonment. "
      comments:
      - number: 1:15
        content: "  His name means \u201Cfugitive.\u201D      His name means \u201Cborn
          of Hermes,\u201D a pagan god.    "
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Nevertheless, so many times Onesiphorus [[COMMENT(0)]] was like a
        breath of fresh air to me and never seemed to be ashamed of my chains. May
        our Lord Jesus bestow compassion and mercy upon him and his household. '
      comments:
      - number: 1:16
        content: "  His name means \u201Cone who brings profit\u201D or \u201Cprofitable\u201D
          or \u201Chelp-bringer.\u201D The Orthodox tradition recognizes Onesiphorus
          as one of the seventy disciples chosen and sent by Jesus to preach. He
          became a bishop at Colophon (Asia Minor) and later at Corinth. Both the
          Orthodox and Roman Catholic churches hold that he died a martyr outside
          of Ephesus in the city of Parium.    "
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For when he arrived in Rome, he searched and searched for me until
        he found out where I was being held, so that he could minister to me, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: just like he did so wonderfully as I rested in his house [[COMMENT(0)]]
        while in Ephesus, as you well know.May Jesus, our Master, give him abundant
        mercy in the day he stands before him.
      comments:
      - number: 1:18
        content: '  This is an alternate translation of the Aramaic words found in
          v.  . This translation has placed them here for the sake of the English
          narrative.  '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Grace to Overcome'
      title: Grace to Overcome
      number: 1
      content: "Timothy, my dear son, [[COMMENT(0)]] live your life empowered by
        God\u2019s free-flowing grace, which is your true strength, found in the
        anointing of Jesus and your union with him! "
      comments:
      - number: 2:1
        content: "  The Greek text literally means \u201Cmy little child,\u201D and
          is used as a term of endearment.    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And all that you\u2019ve learned from me, confirmed by the integrity
        of my life, [[COMMENT(0)]] deposit into faithful leaders who are competent
        to teach the congregations the same revelation."
      comments:
      - number: 2:2
        content: "  Or \u201Cby way of many witnesses.\u201D These \u201Cwitnesses\u201D
          could be those people who also heard Paul\u2019s teaching, or it may refer
          to the prophetic confirmations of the truth he taught to Timothy.    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Overcome every form of evil [[COMMENT(0)]] as a victorious soldier
        of Jesus the Anointed One. '
      comments:
      - number: 2:3
        content: "  As translated from the Aramaic. The Greek says \u201Csuffer hardships.\u201D    "
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: For every soldier called to active duty must divorce himself from
        the distractions of this world so that he may fully satisfy the one who chose
        him.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "An athlete who doesn\u2019t play by the rules will never receive
        the trophy, so remain faithful to God! [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 2:5
        content: '  Supplied by the context to complete the ellipsis.    '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: The farmer who labors to produce a crop should be the first one to
        be fed from its harvest.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Carefully consider all that I\u2019ve taught you, and may our Lord
        inspire you with wisdom and revelation in everything you say and do. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But make Jesus, the Anointed One, your focus in life and ministry.
        For he came to earth as the descendant of David and rose from the dead, according
        to the revelation of the gospel that God has given me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "This is the reason I am persecuted and imprisoned by evildoers, [[COMMENT(0)]]
        enduring the suffering of these chains\u2014but the Word of God can never
        be chained! "
      comments:
      - number: 2:9
        content: "  The Greek text means \u201Cimprisoned as a criminal.\u201D However,
          the Aramaic word used here for \u201Cpersecuted\u201D can also be translated
          \u201Ccrucified.\u201D Perhaps Paul is giving a prophecy of what would
          come. Later, Paul was indeed martyred either by crucifixion or beheading
          for his faith in Christ.    "
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: I endure all these hardships for the benefit of the chosen ones [[COMMENT(0)]]
        in Christ so that they may also discover the overcoming life that is in Jesus
        Christ, and experience a glory that lasts forever!
      comments:
      - number: 2:10
        content: "  The Greek word here for \u201Cchosen\u201D has embedded within
          it the word  . God\u2019s chosen ones have been chosen by the word of God
          to become a living word sent from his mouth to reveal the message of their
          destiny.    "
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'You can trust these words:If we were joined with him in his death,
        then we are joined with him in his life! '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'If we are joined with him in his sufferings, [[COMMENT(0)]] then
        we will reign together with him in his triumph. But if we disregard him,
        then he will also disregard us. '
      comments:
      - number: 2:12
        content: "  An alternate Aramaic translation could read \u201CIf we preach
          the kingdom, we shall rule with him.\u201D    "
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: But even if we are faithless, he will still be full of faith, for
        he never wavers in his faithfulness to us! [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 2:13
        content: "  Or \u201Che will not be unfaithful to himself.\u201D    "
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Be committed to teach the believers all these things when you are
        with them in the presence of the Lord. Instruct them to never be drawn into
        meaningless arguments, or tear each other down with useless words that only
        harm others.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: Avoid False Teachings'
      title: Avoid False Teachings
      number: 15
      content: Always be eager [[COMMENT(0)]] to present yourself before God as a
        perfect and mature minister, without shame, as one who correctly explains
        the Word of Truth.
      comments:
      - number: 2:15
        content: "  An alternate Aramaic translation is \u201CDon\u2019t become frustrated.\u201D
          The Greek word is  , an aorist imperative verb that could be translated,
          \u201CHurry and keep on hurrying,\u201D or \u201CConsider it a serious
          matter and keep on considering it something serious to present yourself
          before God.\u201D    "
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And avoid empty chatter and worthless words, [[COMMENT(0)]] for they
        simply add to the irreverence of those who converse in that manner. '
      comments:
      - number: 2:16
        content: "  The Greek text could be translated \u201Cavoid corrupt and useless
          speakers,\u201D referring not to the words themselves, but to those who
          teach the flock. See v.  .    "
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For the words of Hymenaeus [[COMMENT(0)]] and Philetus are like gangrene,
        they have already spread their poison to many. '
      comments:
      - number: 2:17
        content: '  See the first footnote for  .    '
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: They are lost to the truth and teach gross error when they teach that
        the resurrection of the dead has already passed. [[COMMENT(0)]] They are
        guilty of subverting  the faith of some believers.
      comments:
      - number: 2:18
        content: "  The Aramaic can be translated \u201Cnever going to happen.\u201D     
          The Greek literally means \u201Cturning upside down the faith of some.\u201D    "
    - name: '19: Be a Pure Container of Christ'
      title: Be a Pure Container of Christ
      number: 19
      content: "But the firm [[COMMENT(0)]] foundation of God has written upon it
        these two inscriptions: \u201CThe Lord God recognizes those who are truly
        his!\u201D  and, \u201CEveryone who worships the name of the Lord Jesus 
        must forsake wickedness!\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: 2:19
        content: "  Or \u201Ctrue.\u201D An alternate Aramaic translation of this
          verse could read \u201Cthat resurrection is the firm foundation,\u201D
          referring to v.  .      See  .      Or \u201CLord.\u201D By implication
          it is the Lord Jesus.      An alternate Aramaic translation could read
          \u201CHe will save from wickedness.\u201D    "
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'In a palace you find many kinds of containers and tableware for many
        different uses. Some are beautifully inlaid with gold or silver, but some
        are made of wood or earthenware; some of them are used for banquets and special
        occasions, and some for everyday use. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: But you, Timothy, must not see your life and ministry this way. Your
        life and ministry must not be disgraced, for you are to be a pure container
        of Christ and dedicated to the honorable purposes of your Master, prepared
        [[COMMENT(0)]] for every good work that he gives you to do.
      comments:
      - number: 2:21
        content: "  The Aramaic can be translated \u201Cappreciated.\u201D    "
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Run as fast as you can from all the ambitions and lusts [[COMMENT(0)]]
        of youth; and chase after all that is pure. Whatever builds up your faith
        and deepens your love must become your holy pursuit. And live in peace with
        all those who worship our Lord Jesus with pure hearts.
      comments:
      - number: 2:22
        content: "  The Greek text literally means \u201Crevolutionary desires.\u201D    "
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Stay away from all the foolish arguments of the immature, for these
        disputes will only generate more conflict. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'For a true servant of our Lord Jesus will not be argumentative [[COMMENT(0)]]
        but gentle toward all and skilled in helping others see the truth, having
        great patience toward the immature. '
      comments:
      - number: 2:24
        content: "  An alternate Aramaic translation could read \u201CYou should
          not be argumentative with a true servant of the Lord.\u201D    "
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then with meekness you\u2019ll be able to carefully enlighten those
        who argue with you so they can see God\u2019s gracious gift of repentance
        and be brought to the truth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: This will cause them to rediscover themselves [[COMMENT(0)]] and escape
        from the snare of Satan who caught them in his trap so that they would carry
        out his purposes.
      comments:
      - number: 2:26
        content: "  Or \u201Ccome to their senses.\u201D  "
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Characteristics of the Last Days'
      title: Characteristics of the Last Days
      number: 1
      content: 'But you need to be aware that in the final days the culture of society
        will become extremely fierce. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: People will be self-centered lovers of themselves [[COMMENT(0)]] and
        obsessed with money. They will boast of great things as they strut around
        in their arrogant pride and mock all that is right. They will ignore their
        own families.  They will be ungrateful  and ungodly.
      comments:
      - number: 3:2
        content: "  The Aramaic can be translated \u201Cmen will look out only for
          themselves.\u201D      Or \u201Cdisloyal to their people.\u201D The Greek
          is \u201Cdisobedient to parents.\u201D      The Aramaic can be translated
          \u201Crejecters of grace.\u201D    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'They will become addicted to hateful and malicious slander. [[COMMENT(0)]]
        Slaves to their desires, they will be ferocious, belligerent haters of what
        is good and right. '
      comments:
      - number: 3:3
        content: "  Because this phrase is also the description of the devil (the
          accuser or slanderer), it could be translated \u201Cthey will be devils.\u201D    "
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: With brutal treachery, they will act without restraint, bigoted and
        wrapped in clouds of their conceit. They will find their delight in the pleasures
        of this world more than the pleasures of the loving God.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "They may pretend to have a respect for God, but in reality they want
        nothing to do with God\u2019s power. Stay away from people like these! "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For they are the ones who worm their way into the hearts of vulnerable
        women, [[COMMENT(0)]] spending the night with those who are captured by their
        lusts and steeped in sin. '
      comments:
      - number: 3:6
        content: "  An alternate Greek translation could read \u201Cthey intrude
          into households and by their heresies, take prisoners of those who are
          led astray by desires and sins.\u201D The Aramaic, however, is clearly
          speaking of the gross immorality of the last days.    "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: They are always learning but never discover the revelation-knowledge
        of truth.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: History has given us an example of this with the Egyptian sorcerers
        Jannes and Jambres, [[COMMENT(0)]] who stood against Moses in their arrogance.
        So it will be in the last days with those who reject the faith with their
        corrupt minds and arrogant hearts, standing against the truth of God.
      comments:
      - number: 3:8
        content: '  This is a fascinating verse, for Jannes and Jambres are never
          mentioned by name in Exodus. It simply mentions the sorcerers who wanted
          to compete with Moses and his authority. These two names are, however,
          mentioned by Origen, one of the church fathers, who makes reference to
          the Book of Jannes and Jambres, but no complete copies of these books have
          ever been found.    '
    - name: "9: Timothy\u2019s Loyalty"
      title: "Timothy\u2019s Loyalty"
      number: 9
      content: But they will not advance, for everyone will see their madness, just
        as they did with Jannes and Jambres! [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 3:9
        content: "  Implied in the conclusion of Paul\u2019s argument.    "
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "But you, Timothy, have closely followed my example and the truth
        that I\u2019ve imparted to you. You have modeled your life after the love
        and endurance I\u2019ve demonstrated in my ministry by not giving up. The
        faith I have, you now have. What I have hungered for in life has now become
        your longing as well. The patience I have with others, you now demonstrate. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And the same persecutions and difficulties I have endured, you have
        also endured. Yes, you know all about what I had to suffer while in Antioch,
        Iconium, and Lystra. You\u2019re aware of all the persecution I endured there;
        yet the Lord delivered me from every single one of them! "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: For all who choose to live godly as worshipers of Jesus, the Anointed
        One, will also experience persecution.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'But the evil men and sorcerers [[COMMENT(0)]] will progress from
        bad to worse, deceived and deceiving, as they lead people further from the
        truth. '
      comments:
      - number: 3:13
        content: "  Or \u201Cdeceivers.\u201D The Greek word is \u201Csorcerers.\u201D    "
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Yet you must continue to advance in strength with the truth wrapped
        around your heart, being assured by God that he\u2019s the One [[COMMENT(0)]]
        who has truly taught you all these things."
      comments:
      - number: 3:14
        content: "  By implication \u201CGod.\u201D However, some interpret this
          as his teachers.    "
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Remember what you were taught from your childhood from the Holy Scrolls
        [[COMMENT(0)]] which can impart to you wisdom to experience everlasting life
        through the faith of Jesus, the Anointed One! '
      comments:
      - number: 3:15
        content: "  Or \u201Csacred Scriptures.\u201D    "
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'God has transmitted his very substance into every Scripture, [[COMMENT(0)]]
        for it is God-breathed.  It will empower you by its instruction and correction,
        giving you the strength to take the right direction and lead you deeper into
        the path of godliness. '
      comments:
      - number: 3:16
        content: "  Keep in mind that when Paul wrote this he was referring to the
          Torah and all the Old Testament writings. Today, \u201Cevery Scripture\u201D
          would include the New Testament as well.      The Word of God is inspired.
          Scripture is not simply a book that tells about God, it actually contains
          God. His breath is embedded in his Word.  "
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then you will be God\u2019s servant, fully mature and perfectly prepared
        to fulfill any assignment God gives you."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Paul\u2019s Farewell Message"
      title: "Paul\u2019s Farewell Message"
      number: 1
      content: "Timothy, in the presence [[COMMENT(0)]] of our great God and our
        Lord Jesus Christ, the One who is destined to judge both the living and the
        dead by the revelation of his kingdom\u2014I solemnly instruct you to "
      comments:
      - number: 4:1
        content: "  Or \u201Cbefore the eyes of God.\u201D The Greek word is  , which
          could be translated \u201Cwithin eyesight of.\u201D Imagine looking into
          heaven and seeing the eyes of God gazing at you. This is the strength of
          Paul\u2019s charge to Timothy.    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "proclaim the Word of God and stand upon it no matter what! Rise to
        the occasion and preach when it is convenient and when it is not. Preach
        in the full expression of the Holy Spirit [[COMMENT(0)]]\u2014with wisdom
        and patience as you instruct and teach the people."
      comments:
      - number: 4:2
        content: '  As translated from the Aramaic.    '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For the time is coming when they will no longer listen and respond
        to the healing words of truth because they will become selfish and proud.
        They will seek out teachers with soothing words that line up with their desires,
        saying just what they want to hear. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'They will close their ears to the truth and believe nothing but fables
        and myths. [[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: 4:4
        content: "  The Aramaic can be translated \u201Critualistic ceremonies.\u201D    "
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So be alert to all these things and overcome every form of evil.
        Carry in your heart the passion of your calling as a church planter  [[COMMENT(0)]]
        and evangelist, and fulfill your ministry calling. '
      comments:
      - number: 4:5
        content: "  Implied in the concept of being a New Testament evangelist. Apostolic
          missionaries sent out to evangelize were to plant churches wherever they
          ministered. Our contemporary concept of an evangelist is quite different
          than in Paul\u2019s day.      Or \u201Cbeing confident in your ministry.\u201D    "
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And now the time is fast approaching for my release from this life
        and I am ready to be offered as a sacrifice. [[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: 4:6
        content: "  Or \u201Cpoured out as a drink offering.\u201D    "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "I have fought an excellent fight. I have finished my full course
        with all my might and I\u2019ve kept my heart full of faith. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "There\u2019s a crown of righteousness waiting in heaven for me, and
        I know that my Lord will reward me on his day of righteous judgment. And
        this crown is not only waiting for me, but for all who love and long for
        his unveiling. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 4:8
        content: "  Or \u201Csudden appearance.\u201D    "
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Please come as soon as you can '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'since Demas deserted me and has left to go to Thessalonica, for he
        loves his own life. [[COMMENT(0)]] Crescens has gone to Galatia, and Titus
        has gone to Dalmatia. '
      comments:
      - number: 4:10
        content: "  Or \u201Che loves the world.\u201D    "
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: That leaves only Luke with me, so find Mark and bring him with you,
        for he is a tremendous help for me in my ministry.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'I have also dispatched Tychicus to Ephesus to minister there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "When you come, please bring the leather book bag [[COMMENT(0)]] along
        with the books I left in Troas with Carpus\u2014especially the parchment
        scrolls."
      comments:
      - number: 4:13
        content: "  The Aramaic can be translated \u201Ccarrying case.\u201D This
          would have been a bag made of leather or woolen cloth. The Greek text reads
          \u201Cbring the cloak.\u201D The Aramaic words for \u201Cbook\u201D and
          \u201Ccloak\u201D are nearly identical, which would explain the Greek mistranslation
          using \u201Ccloak.\u201D It is fascinating that the aged Paul, nearing
          death, found his heart attached to the manuscripts and books that undoubtedly
          expounded on the Old Testament writings. He knew Jesus intimately, yet
          longed for more revelation of the written Word until his death.    "
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'You need to know that Alexander, [[COMMENT(0)]] the jeweler,  has
        done me great harm. May our Lord give him what he deserves for all he has
        done. '
      comments:
      - number: 4:14
        content: "    means \u201Cprotector of men\u201D or \u201Cman-pleaser.\u201D     
          The word used here can also be \u201Csilversmith,\u201D \u201Cblacksmith\u201D
          or \u201Ccoppersmith.\u201D    "
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Be careful of him, for he arrogantly opposes our ministry.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "At first there was no one I could count on to faithfully stand with
        me\u2014they all ran off and abandoned me\u2014but don\u2019t hold this against
        them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For in spite of this, my Lord himself stood with me, empowering me
        to complete my ministry of preaching to all the non-Jewish nations so they
        all could hear the message and be delivered from the mouth of the lion! [[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: 4:17
        content: "  Or \u201Cthat they will hear that I have been delivered from
          the mouth of the lion.\u201D By implication, the lion is a metaphor for
          the devil.    "
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: And my Lord will continue to deliver me from every form of evil and
        give me life in his heavenly kingdom. May all the glory go to him alone for
        all the ages of eternity!
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Please give my warm regards [[COMMENT(0)]] to Prisca and to Aquila 
        and to Onesiphorus and his family.
      comments:
      - number: 4:19
        content: "  The Aramaic can be translated \u201Cgive peace.\u201D       
          is a diminutive form of Priscilla (\u201Clong life\u201D). She and her
          husband, Aquila (\u201Ceagle\u201D), were tentmakers like Paul. They were
          not only business partners with Paul, but also partners with him in ministry.
          See  ,  ,  ;  ;  .    "
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Erastus has remained in Corinth, but Trophimus I had to leave in Miletus
        due to his illness. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 4:20
        content: '  The Greek word used here can refer to physical or spiritual ailments.    '
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Do your best to come before winter.Eubulus sends his greetings, along
        with Pudens, Linus, [[COMMENT(0)]] and Claudia, and all those in prison with
        me.
      comments:
      - number: 4:21
        content: '  In church history it was widely accepted and stated by Irenaeus
          that Linus was a disciple of Peter and became the bishop of Rome.  '
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: The Lord is within your spirit and his grace overflows to you!Love
        in Christ,Paul
      comments: []
